### 1. **Dockerfile**:
```dockerfile
# Use a lightweight web server image
FROM nginx:alpine

# Copy the HTML file to the web server directory
COPY demo.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

# Expose port 80 for the web server
EXPOSE 80
```

### 2. **docker-compose.yml**:
```yaml
version: '3'

services:
  web:
    build: .
    ports:
      - "8081:80"
```

### 3. **demo.html** (Place in the same directory)
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Details</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f0f0; /* Light background */
        }
        h1 {
            color: #4CAF50; /* Green color */
        }
        p {
            color: #333; /* Dark gray color */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Tamilselvan B T</h1>
    <p>Profession: Software Developer</p>
    <p>Description: Passionate about technology and coding.</p>
</body>
</html>

```

### **Steps to Run**:
1. Place all three files in the same directory.
2. Run `docker-compose up` in the terminal.
3. Open a browser and go to `http://localhost:8080` to view the webpage with your details.
